I disagree entirely.  Look at communism in the Soviet Union.  It was refusal to accept that people have a right to their own productive resources that led to their downfall.  Capitalism has led to greater human evolution, more scientific development, greater GDP, and a higher average standard of living than the more wealth redistributive systems.<br>
<br>
It is socialism that holds back human evolution.<br>
